spanishExample: ¡Sal o llamaré a la policía!
englishTranslation: Get out or I will call the police!

spanishExample: ¡Salgamos de fiesta! Te llamo luego.
englishTranslation: Let’s go out partying! I’ll call you later.

spanishExample: ¡Salgan y nos vemos!
englishTranslation: (plural) Go out and I’ll see ya!

spanishExample: El agua está saliendo rápido.
englishTranslation: The water is coming out fast.

spanishExample: El doctor te llama por algo importante.
englishTranslation: The doctor is calling you because of something important.

spanishExample: El maestro nos dijo eso a todos.
englishTranslation: The teacher said that to all of us.

spanishExample: El policía vio al joven, quien estaba saliendo de la casa.
englishTranslation: The police officer saw the young man, who was leaving the house.

spanishExample: Es la persona más loca a la que he llamado.
englishTranslation: He is the craziest person that I have called.

spanishExample: Ha parecido que su jefe no quiere que ella salga.
englishTranslation: It has seemed like her boss doesn’t want her to go out.

spanishExample: Le pareció que él había salido.
englishTranslation: It seemed to her that he had gone out.

spanishExample: Llámame o no salgo.
englishTranslation: Call me or I don’t come out.

spanishExample: Me llamó la semana pasada y quería salir, así que eso es genial.
englishTranslation: He called me last week and wanted to go out, so that’s great.

spanishExample: Me parece que saldrá después de la fiesta.
englishTranslation: It seems to me that she will exit after the party.

spanishExample: Me parecía que salieron juntos.
englishTranslation: It seemed to me that they went out together.

spanishExample: No me llamo Pedro, así que no me llames así.
englishTranslation: My name isn’t Pedro, so don’t call me that way.

spanishExample: No quiero que salga de fiesta.
englishTranslation: I don’t want her to go out partying.

spanishExample: No salgas con él porque parece viejo.
englishTranslation: Don’t go out with him because he seems old.

spanishExample: No sé cómo salir de este lugar.
englishTranslation: I don’t know how to exit this place.

spanishExample: Nunca sale con ellos, ni siquiera cuando la llaman.
englishTranslation: She never goes out with them, not even when they call her.

spanishExample: Pareces estar solo; tú y ella nunca salen juntos.
englishTranslation: You seem to be alone; you and she never go out together.

spanishExample: Puede parecer que sales todos los días.
englishTranslation: It might seem like you go out every day.

spanishExample: Quiero que parezca más feliz.
englishTranslation: I want her to seem happier.

spanishExample: Quiero que salgamos, pero la última vez que salimos fue mala.
englishTranslation: I want us to go out, but the last time that we went out was bad.

spanishExample: Quiero que salgan conmigo.
englishTranslation: I want them to go out with me.

spanishExample: Saldría contigo, pero me tienes que llamar.
englishTranslation: I would go out with you, but you have to call me.

spanishExample: Salí ayer y fue malo.
englishTranslation: I went out yesterday and it was bad.

spanishExample: Salió esta mañana.
englishTranslation: He went out this morning.

spanishExample: Si llamas a la puerta, puede que salga.
englishTranslation: If you knock on my door, it might be that I come out.

spanishExample: Supongo que las cosas parecen así, pero no salimos juntos.
englishTranslation: I guess things look that way, but we didn’t go out together.
